TO DOS
When user zooms out too far the grid gets squished. Add dynamic DataZoom max extent assignment based on screen size

KEY BEHAVIOURS

On RENDER:
    useMemo fires; fetch room dimension; initailize room param (boundary lines, handles) as REF 
    useMemo fires; initialize baseChartOption (dependent on PROP _styles)
    useMemo fires; initialize chartSeries (using initial Room param)
    useMemo fires; finalize chartOption;

    Fetches Active Container Size
    useEffect fires; initialize DataZoom extent based on initial room param; Protected by Guard to fire only once unless window size change -> to prevent [BUG] unwanted dataZoom reset during other user drag events.

On PROP - WorstQueue: 
    useMemo fires; Computes location register using room boundary
On PROP - Queue:
    useMemo fires; Slice location register to populate scatter plot
On PROP - _style:
    Re-initialize baseChartOption

On EVENT - User Drag:
    echart Graphic update fires; 
        i. updates handles PX location for graphic elements;
        ii. updates room parameters including room boundary, dimensions, handles;
        iii. schedule Location Register recompute via LocVersion and timer;
    useMemo fires (by LocVersion) on timed interval during drag and on drag end; 
        Computes new location register using new room boundary
On EVENT - User Zoom:
    echart Graphic update fires; 
        i. updates handles PX location for graphic elements;
        ii. computes unitPX to rescale symbolSize;
on EVENT - Window Resize:
    echart Graphic update fires:
        i. updates handles PX location for graphic elements;
        ii. computes unitPX to rescale symbolSize;
    useEffect fires:
        i. update DataZoom extent based on REF room param;

On STATE - unitPX:
    useMemo fires; update symbolSize in chartSeries
on STATE - LocVersion:
    useMemo fires; Computes new location register using new room boundary; used to time updates on timer during user drag and on drag end
on STATE - chartReady:
    useEffect fires:
        i. subscribe to echart DataZoom listeners to handle User Drag, Scaling Update update;
        ii subscribe to window resize listeners to handle User Drag, DataZoom view extent, Scaling Update update;

RESOLVED BUGS:
    1. DataZoom Reset:
        implemented guards to update dataZoom extent only once until window resize;
    2. Window Size initialize on 0/-:
        implemented logic to ensure unitPX is always > 0;

ABONDONED FEATURE:
    1. xAixs extend update on User Drag:
        dataZoom view extent reset is too disruptive; opted for initializing a STATIC, LARGE axis extent at start instead;
